Name: Mahshi
Description: Mahshi, also called Mashi or Mashy, is a green dish including many vegetables such as eggplants, zucchini, bell peppers, cabbage, tomatoes, etc., stuffed with a unique filling. The filling contains mainly rice, herbs, spices, tomato sauce, and cinnamon

Name: Molokhia
Description: Made from the leaves of the Corchorus plant or jute mallow, this leafy vegetable takes center stage in a soup

Name: Feteer Meshaltet
Description: It contains many dough layers topped with thousand options of toppings with sweet (coconut, nutella, chocolate, syrup, honey, sugar) or savory (minced meats, cheese, vegetables) flavors

Name: Bamya
Description: This dish features okra, the star ingredient, and tender lamb immersed in a rich tomato sauce

Name: Basbousa
Description: The rich flavors of semolina, yogurt, and coconut. This irresistible confection derives its luscious sweetness from a unique syrup infused with the enchanting essences of orange flowers or rose extract.

Name: Macarona Béchamel
Description: A treat from heaven with three filling layers of casserole. The deepest layer includes boiled Penne pasta. The middle layer is usually beef mixed with tomato sauce and some onions. The top of it is white Béchamel sauce.

Name: Hummus
Description: Hummus is a delectable dip made from mashed chickpeas with other ingredients such as olive oils, garlic, parsley, cumin, tahini, paprika

Name: Shakshouka
Description: Savor the taste of eggs poached in a mouthwatering tomato sauce infused with garlic, bell peppers, onions, green pepper, and olive oil.

Name: Baklava
Description: Baklava features crispy sheets of phyllo pastry meticulously arranged with a medley of chopped nuts, including pistachios, walnuts, and hazelnuts, accompanied by rich butter and aromatic spices.

Name: Baba Ghanoush
Description: Baba Ghanoush, or Baba Ghanouj, with eggplant as the primary ingredient. It also includes olive oil, garlic, lemon juice, and other herbs and spices like Hummus.

Name: Hamam Mahshi
Description: It includes squab (small pigeon) stuffed with freekeh, onions, and seasonings.

Name: Kebab and Kofta
Description: A heavenly union between two of the most delicious dishes ever created – kebab and kofta. Kebab is known for its tender pieces of meat, grilled to perfection on a coal fire, and typically paired with rice, vegetables, or bread.

Name: Fattah
Description: The dish includes a lot of flatbread pieces dipped in various components, which may vary but usually are rice, lamb, and garlic tomato or vinegar sauce

Name: Shawarma
Description: The tantalizing flavors arise from the thin, heavily-spiced slices of meat – be it beef, lamb, chicken, or mutton – pierced and assembled onto a vertical skewer

Name: Konafa
Description: Featuring shredded phyllo pastry layers filled with either cheese or cream, Konafa is a mouthwatering treat that comes in various sizes

Name: Umm Ali
Description: Umm Ali is soaked in a mixture of milk and sugar, resulting in a lighter, milkier texture compared to traditional bread puddings.

Name: Kahk
Description: Creating a brittle yet deliciously delicate experience. Each biscuit can be enjoyed plain or adorned with ornamental patterns and designs.

Name: Qatayef
Description: This dish includes mini deep-fried semolina-yeast pancakes filled with cream and nuts.

Name: Roz Bel Laban
Description: Includes short-grain rice, rose water, butter, milk, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg, and sugar.

Name: Ghorayeba
Description: Made from three common ingredients: flour, ghee, and sugar in powder form.

Name: Kushari
Description: Kushari is a very delicious vegan dish from the legendary Egyptian culinary dating back to the early days of the Islamic era in Egypt. It consists of food consists of rice, lentils, onions, garlic, chickpeas, and tomato sauce
